To control nothing is to control everything; as one's scope waxes, so too does ones mastery wane.

The instinct to try to know the unknowable, to stare into the abyss, is core to the Foundation's ideology, yet is not infallible. 

Sometimes we aren't up to the challenge, some things are just bigger than us, and render us humbled in our defeat. 

And yet if not us, then who?


We must learn to go against our grain. To be satisfied with not knowing, to lose day in and day out and return tomorrow to fail again.

In the face of unpossiblitiy we must remain unspired to go on all the same.

